# LocalCA-Go Project Overview

LocalCA is a self-hosted Certificate Authority (CA) solution for managing SSL/TLS certificates in local network environments. The project has both a Go backend and a Next.js frontend.

## Project Structure

- [main.go](mdc:main.go) - Application entry point that initializes services and starts the HTTP/HTTPS servers
- [pkg/](mdc:pkg) - Core Go backend packages
  - [certificates/](mdc:pkg/certificates) - Certificate generation and management
  - [config/](mdc:pkg/config) - Configuration loading and management
  - [email/](mdc:pkg/email) - Email notification system
  - [handlers/](mdc:pkg/handlers) - HTTP request handlers
  - [storage/](mdc:pkg/storage) - Certificate storage management
  - [acme/](mdc:pkg/acme) - ACME protocol support for automated certificate issuance
- [app/](mdc:app) - Next.js frontend application
  - [page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main dashboard page
  - [create/](mdc:app/create) - Certificate creation UI
  - [certificates/](mdc:app/certificates) - Certificate management UI
  - [settings/](mdc:app/settings) - Application settings UI
  - [api/](mdc:app/api) - API routes for frontend-backend communication
- [components/](mdc:components) - React components for the frontend UI
- [data/](mdc:data) - Data access layer for frontend
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Docker Compose configuration
- [Dockerfile](mdc:Dockerfile) - Backend Docker build instructions
- [Dockerfile.frontend](mdc:Dockerfile.frontend) - Frontend Docker build instructions
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation and setup instructions

